BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 472 Td (4. Its surface temperature is about 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 450 Td (5. The core is even hotter: 27 MILLION degrees Fahrenheit!) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 428 Td (6. Light from the Sun takes 8 minutes and 20 seconds to reach Earth.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 406 Td (7. The Sun is made mostly of hydrogen \(73%\) and helium \(25%\).) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 384 Td (8. Without the Sun, Earth would be a frozen, lifeless rock in space.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 362 Td (9. The Sun will keep shining for about 5 billion more years.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 340 Td (10. Solar flares from the Sun can disrupt electronics on Earth!) Tj ET

