BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 472 Td (4. Extremophiles on Earth prove life can survive in incredible) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 455 Td (   conditions.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 433 Td (5. Mars, Europa \(Jupiter's moon\), and Enceladus \(Saturn's moon\) might) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 416 Td (   harbor microbial life.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 394 Td (6. The universe is 13.8 billion years old - plenty of time for life to) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 10 Tf 80 377 Td (   evolve elsewhere.) Tj ET
